@baseUrl = https://localhost:7038

### 1. Get all books (with availability status)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books
Accept: application/json

### 2. Add a new book (shows persistence — restart the app and it is still there)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Working Effectively with Legacy Code, Vol 1",
  "author": "Michael Feathers",
  "isbn": "978-0131177055"
}

### 3. Check out an available book (book 1) to member 1
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/checkouts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookId": 1,
  "memberId": 1
}

### 4. Try to check out the same book again (should return 409 Conflict)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/checkouts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookId": 1,
  "memberId": 2
}

### 5. Return the checkout we just created (id will be 1 — first generated id in SQL Server)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/checkouts/1/return
Accept: application/json

### 6. Get all overdue checkouts (seeded overdue checkout should appear)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/checkouts/overdue
Accept: application/json

### 7. Dashboard stats
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/checkouts/dashboard
Accept: application/json
